Alembic async migrations for the estimator backend.

Common commands (run from backend/):

  uv run alembic upgrade head
  uv run alembic downgrade -1
  uv run alembic revision -m "describe change"            # blank template
  uv run alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe"    # diff vs ORM metadata
  uv run alembic current
  uv run alembic history

env.py reads the DSN from the app's `config.get_settings().resolved_postgres_dsn`,
so the same alembic invocations work whether you're on the host or inside the
estimator-backend container.
